  "text": "The latissimus dorsi (LD) flap, first described by Tansini in 1896 [CITATION_1] , is a commonly used tissue transfer for volume replacement in breast reconstruction, either for partial or total mastectomy defects. In this era of cosmetic awareness and oncoplastic breast surgery, the conventional technique presents two main concerns: the large back scar and the bulkiness on the lateral chest wall, under the axilla [CITATION_2] .",
